<h1><a name="register"></a></h1></br>
<h4 class="topspace20">Registering a New Account</h4>
<p>
  In order to use the create and edit features of the Sample Tracker you will need to register an account and log 
  in (login is not required to view details of samples  etc). You can register a new account by following the link 
  on the home page. If you have already registered you can sign in** using the link on the home page or using the 
  menu on the top right corner. 
</p>
<p>
	** Note that upon registration the account needs to be authorised by a member of the admin team (they will be automatically 
	notified). This may take a little time. 
</p>



<h1><a name="samplesets"></a></h1></br>
<h4 class="topspace20">Sample Sets</h4>

<p>
A 'Sample Set' refers to a batch of samples that are being collected on a particular sampling day/period, under a single project 
at one facility. For example, a sample set may refer to 50 samples that are collected for project P003 at the EucFACE facility. 
In advance of any targeted sample collection, a researcher should initiate a new sample set in the Sample Tracker and provide upfront 
details of that set (facility, project, etc).      
</p> 
<h5 class="topspace20">Creating a new Sample Set</h5>
<p>
